libcaption
------------------------------------------
libcaption is a small library written in C to aid in the creating and parsing
of closed caption data for use in the twitch player, open sourced under the
MIT license to use within community developed broadcast tools. To maintain
consistency across platforms libcaption aims to implement a subset of EIA608,
CEA708 as supported by the Apple iOS platform.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libcaption-devel-0.8-1bl1
  libcaption0-0.8-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/szatmary/libcaption

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/szatmary/libcaption/archive/refs/tags/v0.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libcaption-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libcaption-0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libcaption-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcaption-0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcaption0-0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcaption-devel-0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libcaption)
  /usr/bin/flv+scc.exe
  /usr/bin/flv+srt.exe
  /usr/bin/flv2srt.exe
  /usr/bin/party.exe
  /usr/bin/rollup.exe
  /usr/bin/scc2srt.exe
  /usr/bin/scc2vtt.exe
  /usr/bin/sccdump.exe
  /usr/bin/srt2vtt.exe
  /usr/bin/srtdump.exe
  /usr/bin/ts2srt.exe
  /usr/bin/vttdump.exe
  /usr/bin/vttsegmenter.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libcaption.README
  /usr/share/doc/libcaption/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/libcaption/README.md

(libcaption0)
  /usr/bin/cygcaption-0.dll

(libcaption-devel)
  /usr/include/caption/caption.h
  /usr/include/caption/cea708.h
  /usr/include/caption/eia608.h
  /usr/include/caption/eia608_charmap.h
  /usr/include/caption/mpeg.h
  /usr/include/caption/scc.h
  /usr/include/caption/srt.h
  /usr/include/caption/utf8.h
  /usr/include/caption/vtt.h
  /usr/include/caption/xds.h
  /usr/lib/libcaption.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libcaption.pc

